The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Bhopal, March 10: Curfew was imposed in a town near Ujjain tonight after one person was killed and three injured in police firing during communal clashes over a procession.          
	Indefinite curfew has been clamped. Four persons were injured in the firing, three of them critically, Pawan Jain, Ujjains inspector-general of police, said late tonight.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has ruled there is nothing unconstitutional in the government treating degree and diploma engineers on a par for promotion. A bench rejected an argument by degree holders that such parity violated Article 14 of the Constitution.                   
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): A mother and her son have allegedly committed suicide in Ghaziabad district. Mohit, 20, hanged himself from a ceiling fan because of his poor performance in an exam. Saraswati Devi later hanged herself with the same noose, unable to bear her sons death.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The discovery that a sweeper had been allowed into a surgical team at AIIMS has led to a senior cardiac surgeon being suspended and an inquiry started. The surgeon had allegedly given the sweeper a certificate stating he was qualified to operate a heart-lung machine.                  
	 Nagpur (PTI): Twelve Naxalites were arrested and firearms recovered on Monday in an operation carried out by district police and CRPF. The Naxalites were arrested from Koindur and Aasawandi forest, the police said. Ten rifles, 2kg gelatin, six detonators and other explosives were seized.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): A jawan has been arrested at Jammu railway station for allegedly carrying live cartridges. Sepoy Sanjay Singh was caught after his luggage was scanned at the railway station. He has been handed over to military police for further investigations.                                                                                                                           
